{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/head-neck-cancers-recognition-referral/diagnosis/symptoms-suggestive-of-head-neck-cancers/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"d791f347-5ff5-564e-8c45-2189dc12a97a","slug":"symptoms-suggestive-of-head-neck-cancers","fullItemName":"Symptoms suggestive of head and neck cancers","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2da74180-7b1c-46b7-9aa4-74c0e9061850 --><h2>Symptoms suggestive of head and neck cancers</h2><!-- end field 2da74180-7b1c-46b7-9aa4-74c0e9061850 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 329204ca-a886-499b-989f-8198f2299c79 --><!-- begin field ac77818d-59a8-45a5-82b9-3699ba0b3b0a --><p><strong>Table 2</strong><strong>. </strong>Symptoms suggestive of head and neck cancers.</p><table data-table-id=\"ce001263-ea8d-4cc7-b5a1-acce014f0390\"><thead><tr><th><p>Symptom</p></th><th><p>Possible cancer</p></th><th><p>Referral recommendation</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Lip or oral cavity lump</td><td>Oral</td><td><p>Consider an urgent referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks) for assessment by a dentist</p><p>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral by the dentist (for an appointment within 2 weeks) in people when assessed by a dentist as having a lump on the lip or in the oral cavity consistent with oral cancer</p></td></tr><tr><td>Neck lump (persistent and unexplained)</td><td>Oral</td><td>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td>Neck lump (unexplained), 45 years and over</td><td>Laryngeal</td><td>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td>Hoarseness (persistent and unexplained), 45 years and over</td><td>Laryngeal</td><td>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td>Oral cavity red or red and white patch consistent with erythroplakia or erythroleukoplakia</td><td>Oral</td><td><p>Consider urgent referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks) for assessment by a dentist</p><p>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral by the dentist (for an appointment within 2 weeks) for people when assessed by a dentist as having a red or red and white patch in the oral cavity consistent with erythroplakia or erythroleukoplakia.</p></td></tr><tr><td>Ulceration in the oral cavity (unexplained and lasting for more than 3 weeks)</td><td>Oral</td><td>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td>Thyroid lump (unexplained)</td><td>Thyroid</td><td>Consider a suspected cancer pathway referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\"><strong>Data from:</strong> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-neck-cancers-recognition-referral/references/\">NICE, 2015</a>]</td></tr></tbody></table><!-- end field ac77818d-59a8-45a5-82b9-3699ba0b3b0a --><!-- end item 329204ca-a886-499b-989f-8198f2299c79 -->","topic":{"id":"d8aeca55-824e-5d14-99a2-03d75201d424","topicId":"31afbe15-278a-4fa5-9176-8037cc84e2a6","topicName":"Head and neck cancers - recognition and referral","slug":"head-neck-cancers-recognition-referral","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2021","chapters":[{"id":"5a4e0ab7-b961-5ac5-acf5-588f3e0eb657","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e2ed77e5-6a49-52b3-a7fd-bdd665b1ac76","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ba35a98e-d808-5721-832f-61561bd61a4e","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"34efa250-8c4b-51c0-a8d7-495cb8e50c94","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"1bb4a581-7036-5e5c-9166-7d3b82ddfbf4","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"82c95da8-d952-5a14-ada4-37f7205c1789","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures"